Cell.Data: A structured set of questions and their answers
A structured set of questions and their answers. The questions are ordered and grouped into coherent subsets, corresponding to the structure of the grouping of the underlying questions
To support structured, hierarchical registration of data gathered using digital forms and other questionnaires.
Unique id for this set of answers
A business identifier assigned to a particular completed (or partially completed) questionnaire
Used for tracking, registration and other business purposes
Indicates the Questionnaire resource that defines the form for which answers are being provided
Needed to allow editing of the questionnaire in a manner that enforces the constraints of the original form.
The lifecycle status of the questionnaire answers as a whole.

The information on questionnaires may possibly be gathered during multiple sessions and altered after considered being finished. Questionnaires with just questions may serve as template forms, with the applicable publication statuses
.statusCode (also whether there's a revisionControlAct - and possibly mood to distinguish "in progress" from "published)
The subject of the questionnaire answers. This could be a patient, organization, practitioner, device, etc. This is who/what the answers apply to, but is not necessarily the source of information
Person who received and recorded the answers
Person who received the answers to the questions in the QuestionnaireAnswers and recorded them in the system
Need to know who interpreted the subject's answers to the questions in the questionnaire, and selected the appropriate options for answers.
Mapping a subject's answers to multiple choice options and determining what to put in the textual answer is a matter of interpretation.
The date and/or time that this version of the questionnaire answers was authored
Date Created, Date published, Date Issued, Date updated
Clinicians need to be able to check the date that the information in the questionnaire was collected, to derive the context of the answers.
May be different from the update time of the resource itself, because that is the status of the collection and authoring.
The person who answered the questions
The person who answered the questions about the subject. Only used when this is not the subject him/herself
When answering questions about a subject that is minor, incapable of answering or an animal, another human source is used to answer the questions
Source should be a reference to a Person resource too
Primary encounter during which the answers were collected
Encounter during which this set of questionnaire answers were collected. When there were multiple encounters, this is the one considered most relevant to the context of the answers.
Some institutions track questionnaires under a specific encounter
A group of questions to a possibly similarly grouped set of questions in the questionnaire answers
Need to be able to logically group answers to grouped questions
The Questionnaire itself has one "root" group with the actual contents of the Questionnaire
Identifies the group from the Questionnaire that corresponds to this group in the QuestionnaireAnswers resource.
Groups can repeat in the answers, so a direct 1..1 correspondence may not exist - requiring correspondence by id.
Text that is displayed above the contents of the group
When including text for the questionnaire with the answers, sections may have a section header
On the root group, this is the title of the questionnaire
Additional text for the group, used for display purposes
When including text for the questionnaire, each section may contain additional explanations are background text
The subject this group's answers are about
More specific subject this section's answers are about, details the subject given in QuestionnaireAnswers
Sometimes a group of answers is about a specific participant, artifact or piece of information in the patient's care or record, e.g. a specific Problem, RelatedPerson, Allergy etc.
A sub-group within a group. The ordering of groups within this group is relevant
Reports can consist of complex nested groups
Set of questions within this group. The order of questions within the group is relevant
Identifies the question from the Questionnaire that corresponds to this question in the QuestionnaireAnswers resource.
Groups can repeat in the answers, so a direct 1..1 correspondence may not exist - requiring correspondence by id.
Text of the question as it is shown to the user
When including text for the questionnaire, each question may contain its actual question display text
The respondent's answer(s) to the question
We nest the value because we can't have a repeating structure that has variable type
boolean | decimal | integer | date | dateTime | instant | time | string | Attachment | Coding | Quantity | Reference(Any)
Need to be able to retain a single-valued answer to a question

More complex structures (Attachment, Resource and Quantity) will typically be limited to electronic forms that can expose an appropriate user interface to capture the components and enforce the constraints of a complex data type. Additional complex types can be introduced through extensions.
Nested group, containing nested question for this question. The order of groups within the question is relevant
It is useful to have "sub-questions", questions which normally appear when certain answers are given and which collect additional details.
Groups may either contain questions or groups but not both
The status of the questionnaire answers
The questionnaire the answers are provided for
Encounter during which questionnaire was authored
Lifecycle status of the questionnaire answers
